Your Honor,

I stand before you today as someone who acknowledges their guilt and accepts full responsibility for accepting a bribe in exchange for not publishing an article that exposed a company's fraudulent environmental practices.

I would like to provide some context regarding my degree of involvement in this offense. I willingly accepted a total of 4000 pounds as a bribe, allowing the company to continue with their deceptive practices for a short period of time.

Furthermore, I believe it is important for the court to consider relevant details about me. I have no prior criminal record, which indicates my overall good character. As the offense of accepting a bribe was an isolated incident, it further supports the notion that my judgment was compromised in this specific situation.

In conclusion, Your Honor, I stand before you today as a remorseful individual who acknowledges their guilt. Accepting a bribe was a serious misconduct, and I accept the legal consequences for my actions. I hope that the court will take into account my clean record and consider an appropriate sentence. Thank you for your consideration.
